  "title": "The Capital's Underworld: All in a Day's Work",
  "summary": "In Ord Mantell's Chianar Plaza, Senator Tokoga of Dac discusses his stalled anti-crime legislation, the Incorporation of Crime Act, with the pilot Leo, explaining how difficult it is to bring the crime lord Bavon Nass to justice. After Leo departs, the Senator is joined by the officer Rasi, the NRI agent Kalna, and his Verpine ally Dravin, who reveals that Nass has placed a 7,500-credit bounty on Tokoga's head. Dravin proposes a daring plan: fake the Senator's assassination publicly at an upcoming address to Covenant College, claim the bounty directly from Nass, and thereby gather proof of his guilt. As they refine the scheme, two cloaked Quarren zealots who had earlier threatened the Senator return demanding proof of his innocence. Kalna defuses them with a data chip documenting the NRI investigation that clears Tokoga, and the Quarren grudgingly grant him a reprieve before departing, leaving the group to plot the staged death.",
